      "id": "measurements",
      "title": "What EEG Measures",
      "start": 9.39,
      "end": 21.9,
      "duration": 12.51,
      "text": "EEG measures tiny voltage changes at the scalp caused by large groups of neurons firing together. Electrodes do not read thoughts directly. They detect synchronized electrical activity.",
